In article <strnlghtCDvo4p.1vy@netcom.com> strnlght@netcom.com (David Sternlight) writes:
> Richard Bainter <pug@arlut.utexas.edu> wrote:
> > You mean ANY manufacturer of a cryptographic equipment must register?
> You don't HAVE to register. If it turns out you should have and didn't, you
> can be penalized.

Brilliant. ``You don't HAVE to register'' is entirely content-free.
Sternlight could claim, on the same grounds, that ``you don't HAVE to
avoid murdering people,'' or ``you don't HAVE to pay taxes.''

> If what you're making is a Captain Midnight decoder ring,
> or ROT13, it's unlikely the government would spend the time and money to
> make a case even if they thought there was one.

DTC can impose a half-million dollar civil penalty on someone by simply
_sending a letter_. Not much of an investment of time and money there.

---Dan
